  PROJECT BRIEF
  
  This proposal is based on what was discussed during the meetings between Luca Franco and Matt Kareus on April
  21, 2021.
  
  PROJECT UNDERSTANDING
  
  Luxury Frontiers will assume the role of exclusive lead design firm for the Project and will
  provide full architectural & interior design, related development services and experiential
  programming.
  
  Prior to the design, Luxury Frontiers will also provide advisory services until June 30, 2021 to assist the Project
  Team with Moab pre-concept work pertaining to re-zoning of the land area (Phase A).
  
  We understand that Entrada Camps and Conservation LLC (“Owner”) plans to develop an all-inclusive, worldclass lodge inspired by the iconic safari camps of Africa in a 550 acre private nature preserve located in Moab, the
  heart of Utah’s legendary red rock canyon country. This project will be the first of a potential circuit of camps and
  lodges across North America. The owner aims at developing a portfolio of ecolodges and land-based tourism
  projects throughout North America. Additionally, luxury tented camps deliver the comfort of a luxury hotel while
  providing guests with the opportunity to connect with nature in simple yet profoundly meaningful ways.
  
  The Client is pursuing a new mode of truly experiential and immersive tourism in the American West in
  collaboration with communities, conservationists, architects, designers, builders, hospitality professionals, and
  investors. The Moab site will provide guests with a comfortable and sophisticated base from which to explore the
  fascinating and beautiful landscapes fo southeastern Utah’s legendary country canyon. All development will be
  underpinned by Luxury Frontiers’ philosophy of ’treading lightly on the earth’ and will maintain the standards of
  internationally recognized, award-winning properties.
  
  At this stage, the site in Moab will contain
  
  -Main Areas including an adventure pavilion, a library and research room, food and beverage areas, and
  wellness areas
  
  This letter of intent serves to provide the Client with a high-level understanding of an estimated fee structure and
  terms and conditions of engaging Luxury Frontiers as the principal design firm. The full scope will be clarified in a
  
  * * *
  
  PROJECT PROPOSAL
  
  later stage, but will include i) Architectural Design, ii) Interior Design, iii) Experiential Programming, iv) Project Management, v) Management of tent production, handling and installation, and vi) FF&E Procurement.
  
  Prior to the full design work specified in Phase B, Phase A of the Project will be to provide advisory services to the Client for a nominal fee, for the purpose to assist the Project Team with re-zoning and pre-concept approvals.
  
  # SCOPE OF WORK AND SERVICES
  
  The Project Scope is divided into two Phases.
  
  **PHASE A – PRE RE-ZONING APPROVAL**
  
  1.1 Advisory Services
  1.1.1 Between contract effective date and July 30, 2021, Luxury Frontiers will
  
  - Advise and review preliminary site plan and documentation for submission for re-zoning, with local architect and engineer Project Team
  - Review and provide comments on existing Pitch Deck to Investors
  - Review existing financial model and provide high-level feedback
  - Review and advise on the high level CapEx budget and provide high-level feedback
  - Review and provide comments on current branding exercise
  - Provide general attendance such as attending meetings with stakeholders, prospects, and investors.
    These services do not include any hard deliverables in document format as feedback will be shared via conference calls and electronic communications. Furthermore, services will be ongoing for up to 90 days and will be rendered for a nominal fee of $10,000 USD to be paid upon this LOI execution. Any travel expenses shall be pre-approved and reimbursed.
  
  Contingent upon Re-zoning Approval being gained in August 2021 and closing on the land, Phase B – Full Design and Development services will begin. If Phase B does not begin within LOI Term, this letter of intent is subject to full renegotiation and additional approvals. Below is a sample scope of work and services that can be clarified and ratified in the Phase B project proposal at a later stage.
  
